00:54:26.130 --> 00:54:26.910
It's interesting.

00:54:26.910 --> 00:54:29.720
The well-to-do in
the United States

00:54:29.720 --> 00:54:31.910
underperform in
terms of happiness.

00:54:31.910 --> 00:54:33.820
They're not as happy
as they should be.

00:54:33.820 --> 00:54:36.320
Our culture is not as
happy as it could be.

00:54:36.320 --> 00:54:38.220
And I think it has to
do with power dynamics.

00:54:38.220 --> 00:54:43.660
That people tend to be happier
in more egalitarian cultures.

00:54:43.660 --> 00:54:45.280
There are a lot of
new data showing

00:54:45.280 --> 00:54:49.120
egalitarian cultures have
better physical health, less

00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:51.860
ingroup-outgroup
dynamics and stuff.

00:54:51.860 --> 00:54:56.784
So I think that one of the
things that I could have-- this

00:54:56.784 --> 00:54:58.700
would be a good "New
York Times" op-ed piece--

00:54:58.700 --> 00:55:04.640
is to say, here's how power and
privilege and wealth cost you,

00:55:04.640 --> 00:55:10.640
right, which is we show you lose
a little bit of your kindness

00:55:10.640 --> 00:55:11.590
toward other people.

00:55:11.590 --> 00:55:14.780
And that's one of the most
rewarding things in human life,

00:55:14.780 --> 00:55:15.280
right?

00:55:15.280 --> 00:55:19.100
When you're on your deathbed--
I always think like this.

00:55:19.100 --> 00:55:20.570
And people are like, oh, god.

00:55:20.570 --> 00:55:21.390
Where's he going?

00:55:21.390 --> 00:55:23.973
I get my Berkeley undergrads--
when you're on your death bed--

00:55:23.973 --> 00:55:27.517
and they're like, I
don't like this class.

00:55:27.517 --> 00:55:29.600
You're going to be thinking
about the kind things.

00:55:29.600 --> 00:55:31.270
And that's what lasts, right?

00:55:31.270 --> 00:55:34.740
And privilege and power
deprive you of that,

00:55:34.740 --> 00:55:37.720
as one example that
those paradoxes

00:55:37.720 --> 00:55:39.480
that we can bring into focus.

00:55:39.480 --> 00:55:41.690
And I think the hedonic
treadmill is very true.

00:55:41.690 --> 00:55:44.900
We just stop enjoying the
everyday joys and focus

00:55:44.900 --> 00:55:46.590
on other things.

00:55:46.590 --> 00:55:48.149
Great connection.

00:55:48.149 --> 00:55:49.690
